0Carlsen%20on%20a%20popular%20recap%20stream%2C%20analysing%20the%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECarlsen%20said%20he%20was%20a%20bit%20surprised%20by%20how%20the%20match%20unfolded%20with%20most%20of%20the%20games%20ending%20in%20draw.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20something%20that%20was%20bit%20unexpected%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20thought%20that%20Gukesh%20was%20a%20favourite%20to%20win%20the%20match%20but%20this%20was%20a%20game%20that%20never%20really%20took%20off%2C%20Gukesh%20was%20doing%20a%20great%20job%20of%20keeping%20the%20position%20alive%20and%20suddenly%20it%20was%20all%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20Carlsen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20really%20good%20thing%20for%20him%2C%20he%20has%20the%20title%20now%20for%20two%20years%2C%20winning%20this%20championship%20is%20extremely%20motivating%20so%20there%20is%20a%20very%20good%20chance%20that%20he%20is%20going%20to%20go%20for%20a%20great%20run%20of%20results%20now%20and%20probably%20become%20the%20number%20two%20player%20now%20and%20may%20be%20number%20one%20in%20the%20not%20so%20distant%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20post-event%20press%20conference%2C%20Gukesh%20stated%20that%20he%20would%20love%20to%20fight%20it%20out%20against%20Carlsen%20at%20some%20point.%20The%20Norwegian%20maverick%20decided%20not%20to%20defend%20his%20title%20in%202023%20after%20winning%20the%20world%20championship%20in%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWinning%20World%20Chess%20Championship%20does%20not%20mean%20I%20am%20the%20best%20player%2C%20obviously%20that%20is%20Magnus%20Carlsen.%20I%20want%20to%20reach%20the%20level%20Magnus%20has%20achieved%2C%26quot%3B%20Gukesh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%20playing%20against%20Magnus%20in%20the%20world%20championship%20would%20be%20amazing%2C%20it%20would%20be%20the%20toughest%20challenge%20there%20is%20in%20chess.%20It%20is%20up%20to%20Magnus%2C%20but%20I%20would%20love%20to%20test%20myself%20against%20the%20