-chipmaking-woes-2024-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DToday%252C%2520it%2520would%2520be%2520better%2Cincredibly%2520hard%2520to%2520run%2520efficiently.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efabs%20hold%20important%20geopolitical%20significance%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20both%20Intel%20and%20the%20US.%20The%20manufacturing%20part%20of%20the%20business%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-ceo-pat-gelsinger-turnaround-plan-aws-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweighs%20on%20the%20company's%20financial%3C%2Fa%3E%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20far%20as%20does%20it%20ever%20fully%20separate%3F%20I%20think%20that's%20an%20open%20question%20for%20another%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Zinsner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e01118a2-eb27-449b-8210-7e516120d836%5C%22%3EAlready%20in%20motion%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20co-CEOs%20made%20it%20clear%20a%20final%20decision%20on%20a%20potential%20break-up%20has%20not%20been%20made%2C%20Zinsner%20outlined%20a%20series%20of%20moves%20already%20in%20progress%20that%20could%20make%20a%20split%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20already%20run%20the%20businesses%20separately%2C%20but%20we%20are%20going%20down%20the%20path%20of%20creating%20a%20subsidiary%20for%20Intel%20Foundry%20as%20part%20of%20the%20overall%20Intel%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Zinsner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20company%20is%20forming%20a%20separate%20operational%20board%20for%20Intel%20Foundry%20and%20separating%20the%20operations%20and%20inventory%20management%20software%20for%20the%20two%20sides%20of%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20a%20permanent%20CEO%20is%20appointed%20by%20the%20board%2C%20the%20co-CEOs%20will%20manage%20most%20areas%20of%20the%20company%20together%2C%20but%20Zinsner%20alone%20will%20manage%20the%20Foundry%20business.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20foundry%20aims%20to%20build%20a%20contract%20manufacturing%20business%20for%20other%20chip%20designers.%20Due%20to%20th